1. get the mac model from system report
2. make a copy of Bootcamp Assistant then modify the info.plist,
   remove pre from "preUEFI" and "preUSB" and add your model to the array
3. then do the bootcamp installation
4. if you get problems like 'no bootable devices' just restart and 
   hold option key to boot into windows(EFI boot)
5. if you get issues like 'windows can only install on GPT disk', 
   then go back macos, earse the bootcamp partitaion as mac extended journaled
6. get into the windows installation then remove bootcamp disk then done!
